snippet.title: M.Sc. in Computational Linguistics Structure || CTRANS || DBRAU, Agra
snippet.description: An overview of the structure of M.Sc. in Computational Linguistics at the Centre for Transdisciplinary Studies, Dr. Bhimrao Ambedkar University, Agra, to be started from Session 2020-21. It will be co-taught by professors from 4 departments - Linguistics, Maths, Statistics and Computer Science - and collaborators from industry and other institutions such as Microsoft Research, Panlingua and IIT-KGP. For more information and application for admission, visit the Centre website - http://www.ctrans.in
